<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 13 at 5:28PM MDT until June 13 at 5:45PM MDT by NWS Spokane</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM PDT
FOR SOUTH CENTRAL BONNER AND NORTH CENTRAL KOOTENAI COUNTIES...
At 428 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles east of
Athol, or 20 miles south of Sandpoint, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Bayview and Granite.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
